The case of the two men accused of fatally shooting Kgomotso Diale, has been postponed to Friday next week in the Protea Magistrate’s Court in Soweto. Tebogo Molapo and Mokhabi Ngoanapudi are accused of gunning down Diale at the Chicken Farm informal settlement during a confrontation regarding cable theft in Pimville last month. The matter was postponed on Wednesday to allow the accused to secure legal representation. They are facing various charges including two counts of murder, six counts of attempted murder and two counts of possession of unlicensed firearms and ammunition. Kgomotso Diale’s family seeks answers, hopes his death will not be in vain In April, the family of the slain Soweto man said they hope his death will not be in vain. Diale’s family made the appeal to Police Minister Bheki Cele who visited the family in Pimville Soweto to pay his respects earlier today. Police minister Bheki Cele visited the 45-years-old family’s home and another survivor before addressing Pimville residents. Police Minister Bheki Cele addresses Kliptown and Pimville residents [ 20 April 2022] 